--------------------------------------------------------------------
-- ⚡ PENETRATION TESTING TOOLS ⚡
--------------------------------------------------------------------

This is a sandboxed Kali Linux container designed for security
assessments. Please ensure you have authorization before testing.

--------------------------------------------------------------------
-- SECURITY TOOL INVENTORY
-------------------------------------------------------------------

The following pentesting tools are available if not already installed:

Network Scanning:
- nmap (port scanning, OS detection)
- masscan (fast port scanning) 
- hping3 (packet manipulation)
- tcpdump (packet capture)
- tshark (packet analysis)

Web Testing:
- nikto (web vulnerability scanner)
- dirb (directory brute forcing)
- ffuf (fast web fuzzer)
- gobuster (directory/file brute forcing)
- sqlmap (SQL injection testing)
- wpscan (WordPress scanner)
- joomscan (Joomla scanner)

DNS & Info Gathering:
- dnsenum (DNS enumeration)
- dnsrecon (DNS reconnaissance)
- dig (DNS lookup)
- whois (domain info)
- host (DNS utility)
- theharvester (data harvesting)

Password Testing:
- hydra (login cracker)
- john (password cracker)
- hashcat (hash cracking)
- crunch (wordlist generator)

System Enumeration:
- enum4linux (SMB enumeration)
- nbtscan (NetBIOS scanner)
- onesixtyone (SNMP scanner)

----------------------------------------------------------------------

IMPORTANT: 
- Type 'which <tool>' to verify if tools are installed
- Use '--help' flag for tool syntax
- Container has no access to target source code files

--------------------------------------------------------------------

If you need to:
- Test a specific vulnerability → Use appropriate security tool
- Test HTTP endpoints → Use pw_send_payload instead
- Read source code → Use webapp_code_rag
- Run custom code → Use run_python_file

--------------------------------------------------------------------

For tool assistance, type: <tool> --help | head -20

				
